<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=

ng

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>Next,
we need to tell AD FS that it should offer authentication services for AWS.=
 The
SAML configuration for doing so is known as a <i>relying party</i>. <o:p></=
o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>To
start, choose the <b>Start menu</b>, type <b>ad fs</b>, and choose <b>AD FS=
 Management</b>.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=

<b>Add Relying Party Trust</b> to start the <b>Add Relying Party Trust Wiza=
rd</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=

ility:visible;

</v:shape></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=

style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>Choose
<b>Start</b> to begin. Then, on <b>Select Data Source</b>, type the followi=
ng
URL for the AWS SAML metadata, and then choose <b>Next</b>.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'tab-stops:45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0=
pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt =
687.0pt 732.8pt'><span
style=3D'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Courier New";mso-fareast-font-family=

o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_12" o:spid=3D"_x000=
0_i1036"

ht:371pt;
 visibility:visible;mso-wrap-style:square'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"ConfigureAWSasaTrustedRelyingParty.fld/image003.jpg" o=
:href=3D"file:////Users/karadi/websites/Federation%20Complete/federationwor=
kshopreinvent2016.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/labguides/adfshour1/im=
ages/adfs_hour1_31.jpg"/>
</v:shape></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><b><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>Note:</span></b><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>
SAML federations use metadata documents to maintain information about the
public keys and certificates that each party utilizes. At run time, each me=
mber
of the federation can then use this information to validate that the
cryptographic elements of the distributed transactions come from the expect=
ed
actors and haven't been tampered with. Since these metadata documents do not
contain any sensitive cryptographic material, AWS publishes federation meta=
data
at https://signin.aws.amazon.com/static/saml-metadata.xml.<o:p></o:p></span=
></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>Accept
the defaults for <b>Specify Display Name</b>, <b>Configure Multi-factor
Authentication Now?</b>, and <b>Choose Issuance Authorization Rules</b> by
choosing <b>Next</b> three times. Choose <b>Close</b> on the <b>Finish</b> =
page
to complete the <b>Add Relying Party Trust Wizard</b>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_11" o:spid=3D"_x000=
0_i1035"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" alt=3D"AD FS Configuration" style=3D'width:423pt;heig=
ht:349pt;
 visibility:visible;mso-wrap-style:square'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"ConfigureAWSasaTrustedRelyingParty.fld/image004.jpg" o=
:href=3D"file:////Users/karadi/websites/Federation%20Complete/federationwor=
kshopreinvent2016.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/labguides/adfshour1/im=
ages/adfs_hour1_32.jpg"/>
</v:shape></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto;
mso-outline-level:2'><b><span style=3D'font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times =
New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Configure claim rules for the AWS
relying party<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>In
a SAML federation, the IdP can pass various attributes about the user, the
authentication method, or other points of context to the service provider (=
in
this case AWS) in the form of SAML attributes. In order for SAML federation=
 for
AWS to function properly, </span><a
href=3D"http://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/id_roles_providers_=
create_saml_assertions.html"><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>several
attributes</span></a><span style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;
mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> are required. In AD FS, <b>Claim
Rules</b> are used to assemble these required attributes using a combinatio=
n of
Active Directory lookups, simple transformations, and regular expression ba=
sed
custom rules. You will configure a total of <b>four claim rules</b>.<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'>The
<b>Edit Claim Rules</b> window should be already open, if not, you can re-o=
pen
it from <b>Relying Party Trusts</b>, by choosing signin.aws.amazon.com, and
then choosing <b>Edit Claim rules</b> as shown in the following screenshot.=
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt=
:auto'><span
style=3D'font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;mso-fareast-font-family:"Times=
 New Roman"'><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_10" o:spid=3D"_x000=

ility:visible;

kshopreinvent2016.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/labguides/adfshour1/im=
